## 1. Dijkstra’s Algorithm for Vehicle Route Optimization

This example:
- Represents a road network as a weighted graph.
- Finds the shortest path from a start location to a destination.
- Can be extended to multiple vehicles by running Dijkstra once per vehicle or using multi-vehicle heuristics.

```java
import java.util.*;

public class VehicleRouteOptimizer {

    /**
     * Graph node representing a location (e.g., intersection, depot, customer).
     */
    private static class Node {
        private final String id;
        private final double distance; // distance from source (for Dijkstra)

        public Node(String id, double distance) {
            this.id = id;
            this.distance = distance;
        }

        @Override
        public String toString() {
            return "Node{id='" + id + "', distance=" + distance + "}";
        }
    }

    /**
     * Edge between two nodes with a travel cost (e.g., distance, time).
     */
    private static class Edge {
        private final String from;
        private final String to;
        private final double cost;

        public Edge(String from, String to, double cost) {
            this.from = from;
            this.to = to;
            this.cost = cost;
        }
    }

    /**
     * Simple adjacency list graph.
     */
    private static class Graph {
        private final Map<String, List<Edge>> adj = new HashMap<>();

        public void addEdge(String from, String to, double cost) {
            adj.computeIfAbsent(from, k -> new ArrayList<>()).add(new Edge(from, to, cost));
        }

        public List<Edge> getEdges(String node) {
            return adj.getOrDefault(node, Collections.emptyList());
        }
    }

    /**
     * Dijkstra's algorithm to find the shortest path from start to end.
     *
     * @param graph   the road network graph
     * @param start   starting location ID
     * @param end     destination location ID
     * @return list of node IDs in order, or empty list if no path exists
     */
    public static List<String> dijkstra(Graph graph, String start, String end) {
        if (!graph.adj.containsKey(start)) {
            return Collections.emptyList();
        }

        Map<String, Double> dist = new HashMap<>();
        Map<String, String> prev = new HashMap<>();
        PriorityQueue<Node> pq = new PriorityQueue<>(Comparator.comparingDouble(n -> n.distance));

