To create a lightweight .NET microservice that sends an email through SMTP using gRPC, you can follow these steps:

1. Create a new gRPC project.
2. Define the service in a .proto file.
3. Implement the service in a .NET class.
4. Host the service with a gRPC server.
5. Consume the service from another .NET project.

Here's an example of each step:

1. Create a new gRPC project:
```sh
dotnet new grpc -o EmailService
cd EmailService
```
1. Define the service in a .proto file:

Create a new file called "email.proto" in the "Protos" folder and add the following code:
```proto
syntax = "proto3";

package email;

service EmailService {
  rpc SendEmail (EmailRequest) returns (EmailResponse);
}

message EmailRequest {
  string from = 1;
  string to = 2;
  string subject = 3;
  string body = 4;
}

message EmailResponse {
  bool success = 1;
}
```
1. Implement the service in a .NET class:

Create a new file called "EmailServiceImpl.cs" and add the following code:
```csharp
using System;
using System.Net.Mail;
using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Grpc.Core;
using email;

namespace EmailService
{
    public class EmailServiceImpl : EmailService.EmailServiceBase
    {
        private readonly string SmtpServer = "your_smtp_server";
        private readonly int SmtpPort = 587;
        private readonly string SmtpUsername = "your_username";
        private readonly string SmtpPassword = "your_password";

        public override async Task<EmailResponse> SendEmail(EmailRequest request, ServerCallContext context)
        {
            try
            {
                using (var client = new SmtpClient(SmtpServer, SmtpPort))
                {
                    client.Credentials = new System.Net.NetworkCredential(SmtpUsername, SmtpPassword);
                    client.EnableSsl = true;

                    var mailMessage = new MailMessage(request.From, request.To, request.Subject, request.Body);
                    await client.SendMailAsync(mailMessage);

                    return new EmailResponse { Success = true };
                }
            }
            catch (Exception)
            {
                return new EmailResponse { Success = false };
            }
        }
    }
}
```
1. Host the service with a gRPC server:

